
[1]concubine

   CONCUBINE, n. [L., to lie together, to lie down.]

   1. A woman who cohabits with a man, without the authority of a legal
   marriage; a woman kept for lewd purposes; a kept mistress.

   2. A wife of inferior condition; a lawful wife, but not united to the
   man by the usual ceremonies, and of inferior condition. Such were Hagar
   and Keturah, the concubines of Abraham; and such concubines were
   allowed by the Roman laws.
